<br>
And that's when it all went downhill.<br>
<br>
Festering boils swelled up, encamping themselves all over the back of my plaguing hands, though at the sight you would not recognize them as hands, but as vile, decaying clumps of spoiled rodent meat. My vision began to melt into pain until I could not see, but my body could feel hellfire itself nearing. The infernal flames burned, cauterised and completely incinerated my once livid skin, but no, those flames did not engulf my body and put my burnt, roasting body to rest. <br>
<br>
My eyes... my liquid eyes bust, like an egg being cracked on the side of a pan. The &quot;yolk&quot; forcefully poured onto my tongue, sent searing throbs of the worst torment to my battered mind. Only once I had gained some feeling in my tongue again did the rusted, blunt blade hack it out and put a nail in it, impaling it against the wall.<br>
<br>
A seething voice, though it was no more than a crucifying cackle, spoke it's words in my mind. Every word it uttered was a thousand images, each spawning an unique nightmare, contaminating my mind, infecting my thoughts. <br>
<br>
I felt a terrible tearing, I think my unneeded eyelids were torn off, but I have not the hands to feel nor the eyes to see. A wicked hand puntured my lungs and stole my air; it's claws, tipped with a poison so lasting that eternity itself could not claim me, and the venom flowed through my tainted blood.<br>
<br>
I was barely conscience, but I remember... My bones sucked dry of my marrow, then shattered by what I swore was an unholy maul; and only then were they slowly pulled out of my body. My bruised skull was crushed underneath that demonic maul, sending fragments of bone tearing through my soft brain.<br>
<br>
As my soul rose free, it rose only so far.<br>
<br>
Attached to my leg, an ethereal adamantine chain.<br>
